<item>
            <title>[SYNAPSE-566] Content of Soap 1.1 faultcode not correctly transformed into Soap 1.2 faultcode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SYNAPSE-566</link>
                <project id="12310201" key="SYNAPSE">Synapse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We are using something like the following synapse configuration to convert soap 1.2 messages to soap 1.1 messages&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;proxy name=&quot;SynapseProxy&quot; transports=&quot;http, https&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;target&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
		&amp;lt;endpoint name=&quot;Soap11Webservice&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                        &amp;lt;address uri=&quot;http://localhost/MySoap11Webservice&quot; format=&quot;soap11&quot; /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                &amp;lt;/endpoint&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
	&amp;lt;/target&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/proxy&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is all working well except when we are receiving a Soap Fault from the &apos;MySoap11Webservice&apos; like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;?xml version=&apos;1.0&apos; encoding=&apos;utf-8&apos;?&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;SOAP-ENV:Envelope xmlns:SOAP-ENV=&quot;http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;SOAP-ENV:Body&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;SOAP-ENV:Fault&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                         &amp;lt;faultcode&amp;gt;SOAP-ENV:Server&amp;lt;/faultcode&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
                         &amp;lt;faultstring&amp;gt;Something went wrong&amp;lt;/faultstring&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;/SOAP-ENV:Fault&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;/SOAP-ENV:Body&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/SOAP-ENV:Envelope&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Synapse transforms this message using the org.apache.synapse.core.axis2.SOAPUtils into the following soap 1.2 message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;?xml version=&apos;1.0&apos; encoding=&apos;utf-8&apos;?&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;soapenv:Envelope xmlns:soapenv=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2003/05/soap-envelope&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;soapenv:Body&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;soapenv:Fault&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;soapenv:Code&amp;gt;&amp;lt;soapenv:Value&amp;gt;SOAP-ENV:Server&amp;lt;/soapenv:Value&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/soapenv:Code&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;soapenv:Reason&amp;gt;&amp;lt;soapenv:Text xml:lang=&quot;en&quot;&amp;gt;Something went wrong&amp;lt;/soapenv:Text&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/soapenv:Reason&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
        &amp;lt;/soapenv:Fault&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
    &amp;lt;/soapenv:Body&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/soapenv:Envelope&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There are 2 problems here:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. In Soap 1.2 Server should be translated to Receiver (also see &lt;a href=&quot;http://java.sun.com/javaee/5/docs/tutorial/doc/bnbhr.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://java.sun.com/javaee/5/docs/tutorial/doc/bnbhr.html&lt;/a&gt; where in Table 19-1 SOAP &apos;Fault Code Values&apos; the other correct fault codes are)&lt;br/&gt;
2. The namespace prefix SOAP-ENV where Server is prefixed with is not known and should be soapenv.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
